.TH "drm_helper_encoder_in_use" 9 "drm_helper_encoder_in_use" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_helper_encoder_in_use \- check if a given encoder is in use
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" drm_helper_encoder_in_use
.BI "(struct drm_encoder *encoder "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "encoder" 12
encoder to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether \fIencoder\fP is with the current mode setting output configuration
in use by any connector. This doesn't mean that it is actually enabled since
the DPMS state is tracked separately.
.SH "RETURN"
True if \fIencoder\fP is used, false otherwise.
